member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.CLS
member.summary: This command clears the Standard Event Status, Operation Status Event, and Questionable Status Event registers, clears the Status Byte and the Error Queue, and if *CLS immediately follows a program message terminator (<NL>), then the output queue and the MAV bit are also cleared.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.ESE
member.summary: This command programs the Standard Event Status Enable register bits. The programming determines which events of the Standard Event Status Event register (see *ESR?) are allowed to set the ESB (Event Summary Bit) of the Status Byte register. A "1" in the bit position enables the corresponding event.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.ESR
member.summary: This query reads the Standard Event Status Event register. Reading the register clears it. The bit configuration is the same as the Standard Event Status Enable register (see *ESE).

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.IDN

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.OPC
member.summary: This command causes the instrument to set the OPC bit (bit 0) of the Standard Event Status register when the instrument has completed all pending operations.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.OPT
member.summary: This query requests the unit to identify any installed options. A 0 indicates no options are installed.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.RCL
member.summary: This command restores the power supply to a state that was previously stored in memory locations 0 through 15 with the *SAV command.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.RST
member.summary: This command resets the power supply to a factory-defined state. This state is defined as follows. Note that *RST also forces an ABORt command.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.SAV
member.summary: This command stores the present state of the power supply to memory locations 0 through 15.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.SRE
member.summary: This command sets the condition of the Service Request Enable Register. This register determines which bits from the Status Byte Register are allowed to set the Master Status Summary (MSS) bit and the Request for Service (RQS) summary bit. A 1 in any Service Request Enable Register bit position enables the corresponding Status Byte Register bit and all such enabled bits then are logically OR-ed to cause Bit 6 of the Status Byte Register to be set.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.STB
member.summary: This query reads the Status Byte register, which contains the status summary bits and the Output Queue MAV bit. Reading the Status Byte register does not clear it. The input summary bits are cleared when the appropriate event registers are read. The MAV bit is cleared at power-on, by *CLS' or when there is no more response data available.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.TRG
member.summary: This command generates a trigger when the trigger source is set to BUS. The command has the same affect as the Group Execute Trigger (<GET>) command.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.TST
member.summary: This query always returns a zero.

member.name: P:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SCPIClass.WAI
member.summary: This command instructs the power supply not to process any further commands until all pending operations are completed. Pending operations are as defined under the *OPC command. *WAI can be aborted only by sending the power supply a Device Clear command.

member.name: T:Agilent.CommandExpert.ScpiNet.AgN5700_A_04_00.SCPI.SRE.SREClass
member.summary: This command sets the condition of the Service Request Enable Register. member.summary:

None - SYST:ERR? queries will not be automatically sent.
ErrorQueryPerCommand - a :SYST:ERR? query will be sent after each command, and after each query that times out.

When setting IgnoredErrors, the input string should contain a list of zero or more items, separated by commas. Each item is either an integer, or a range of the form X:Y where X and Y are integers. The integers can be positive, 0, or negative.
